title: Cross country: Clear Lake shines at state preview meet
text:
The Clear Lake High School varsity boys cross country team placed 10th in the elite gold division at the State Preview meet in Round Rock this past weekend. 
More than 250 teams from the state participated in the event. 
Clear Lake runners and their times included Robert Struthers (15:49), Luke Phillips (16:04), Scott Phillips (16:29), Javi Villarreal (16:41), Hunter Lyde (16:45), Alex Bradley (17:22.2), Joey Bigler (17:22.4), Paxton Laboe (17:30), Julian Martin (17:45) and Joel Phillips (18:42). 
This week, the Falcons host the Clear Lake Invitational Friday morning at Miramar Park in Seabrook. 
On Oct. 15, the District 24-6A cross country meet will be held at the League City Sports Complex.
